  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Fairmont </strong>rooms are spacious at around 33-40m² and have <span>47” HD flat-screen televisions and floor-to-ceiling windows that open to the exterior. They are typically on the 3rd-16th floors and have views overlooking the garden and city skyline. They have one King, one Queen, or two double beds sleeping up to four people.</span></p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Partial Harbour View </strong>rooms are typically on the 4th-23rd floors. These e<span>legant rooms have partial water-views overlooking Vancouver’s working harbour, coastal mountains and cruise ship terminal. They have one King or two double beds sleeping up to four people.</span></p>
<p><span><strong>Signature Harbour View</strong> rooms are typically on the 10th-23rd floors. These premium rooms are east-facing and have spectacular views of the coastal mountains and Vancouver Harbour. They have one King or two double beds sleeping up to four people.</span></p>
<p><strong>Bedroom Facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><span>Cable / satellite TV</span></li>
<li><span>Minibar / fridge</span></li>
<li><span>Tea &amp; coffee making facilities </span></li>
<li><span>Air conditioning</span></li>
<li><span>Safe</span></li>
<li><span>Wi-Fi</span></li>
<li><span>Hairdryer</span></li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
